ensure that all travel arrangements comply with relevant federal government legislation and employer policies, such as employment equity, official languages. 1.5.2 The traveller shall: become familiar with the provisions of this directive;
consult and obtain authorization including blanket travel authority, where applicable, to travel in accordance with the directive;
inform the employer or its suppliers of his/her needs that may require accommodation;
complete and submit travel expense claims with necessary supporting documentation as soon as possible after the completion of the travel.

